              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a place for making gifts or offerings (see {L:γαζοφυλάκιον&lt;SDBG:γαζοφυλάκιον:000001&gt;}[b] - {D:6.141}).</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>offering box</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>According to tradition there were thirteen such offering boxes in the Temple and the receptacles leading down to the boxes were made in the form of trumpets. As a result, the sound of coins falling into the boxes was rather conspicuous.|In {S:04202100400022} it is possible to interpret εἰς τὰ δῶρα not as ‘into the offering boxes’ but as ‘for their gifts,’ thus reflecting a more common meaning of {L:δῶρον&lt;SDBG:δῶρον:000000&gt;}[a] gift ({D:57.84}).</Comments>
